  "prompt": "Are the jobs that president-elect Donald Trump saved in Indiana at the carrier plant Union or non-union?",
  "response": "The jobs that President-elect Donald Trump helped to save at the Carrier plant in Indiana were primarily non-union jobs. At the time, the Carrier plant was a non-union facility, and the agreement involved keeping some jobs in the U.S. rather than moving them to Mexico, where labor costs were lower. The deal was met with both support and criticism, with supporters arguing it helped protect American jobs and critics questioning the efficacy and sustainability of such arrangements.",
